-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-11/oaktree-japan-head-nakamura-said-to-resign-by-middle-of-2013.html
Hiroshi Nakamura, managing director
of Oaktree  Japan , will resign by the middle of this year,
according to a person familiar with the situation.  No replacement will be made, the person said, who asked not
to be identified because the information is private.  Charlotte  Bilney, a Hong Kong-based spokeswoman for Oaktree at public
relations company Citigate Dewe Rogerson, declined to comment.  Oaktree owns 45 percent of  Japan Rental Housing Investments
Inc. (8986)  through AppleRingo Holdings BV and Ringo Residential,
according to a filing to Japanâ€™s Ministry of Finance. The REIT,
which manages 177 apartments with 9,924 units throughout Japan,
gained 83 percent in the past six months.  Oaktree Japan is a unit of Los Angeles-based Oaktree
Capital Management LP, which managed $77.1 billion as of Dec. 31,
2012.  To contact the reporters on this story:
